The paper investigates the role of vanishing point in gaze guidance in free viewing and visual search tasks. This involves analyzing eye fixations and developing a model of bottom-up saliency and vanishing point. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is computer vision (cs.CV), followed by human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). The paper also involves machine learning techniques to develop the combined model, which suggests a possible fit with artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
